Ancestors

Profile last modified 23 May 2024

Biography

Elizabeth, daughter of Jas Arthur Dease & CA A Jerningham, was born on 17 May 1864 and baptised on 18 May 1864 in Mayne, Westmeath, Ireland.[1]

In the 1911 census, Elisabeth (age 46) was a single superior in Convent of The Assumption, 20, 23, 24 and 24A Kensington Square, Kensington S W, Kensington, London, England.[2]

Elizabeth departed from England on 8 December 1925[3]

Elizabeth (age 61) arrived on 14 December 1925 in New York, New York, United States having departed from Southampton, England[4]

Elizabeth (age 69) arrived on 11 August 1933[5]

In the 1939 register, Elizabeth (age 75), Member of Teaching Commercial, was recorded as single in Convent & School of the Assumption Broadway., Sidmouth, Devon, England.[6]

Elizabeth's death (age 87) was registered in the Jul-Aug-Sep quarter of 1951 in the Honiton district.[7]
